<h3>When to Reject a Draft Entirely</h3>
<p>Some drafts are not worth revising. Reject and restart if:</p>
<ul>
<li>The writer missed the brief by more than 30% (wrong topic, wrong angle, wrong audience).</li>
<li>Factual errors are pervasive, not isolated.</li>
<li>The tone is fundamentally misaligned and would require a full rewrite to fix.</li>
<li>Plagiarism or AI-generated content is detected without disclosure.</li>
</ul>
<p>Rejection is expensive. Prevention through better briefs and outlines is cheaper.</p>
<h2>Contracts, IP Rights, and Payment Terms</h2>
<p>Legal protection is not paranoia. It is standard practice. Every writer you hire should sign an agreement before they access your systems or see your strategy.</p>
